trend_summary: Across the sequence, the street grid stays intact while minor infill adds houses and expands commercial roofs near the freeway. A school complex receives a new track-and-turf stadium, and tree cover thickens steadily. Overall land-use remains stable, with only incremental densification.
notable_changes: School athletic area redeveloped into a full track-and-field stadium.
New or enlarged commercial/warehouse roofs appear south of the freeway.
Several vacant or oversized lots infilled with single-family houses.
Street-tree and backyard canopy grows denser neighborhood-wide.
